The paper deals with the problem of person search, which involves pedestrian detection and person re-identification. This is a computer vision problem, hence cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a novel method for feature extraction using two separate CNN streams, which involves modeling foreground person and original image patches individually. This suggests that the paper may also belong to sub-categories such as cs.AI and cs.LG, which deal with machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also evaluates its method on two standard person search benchmarks, which suggests that it may belong to sub-categories such as cs.MM (multimedia) and cs.IR (information retrieval).
